<div class="hero">
  <h1>UK migration statistics are often discussed as if they are one number. They are not.</h1>
  <p class="lede">Migration, immigration, net migration and asylum are different things,
  counted in different ways, over different periods. This site shows what each figure
  actually measures, and what it does not.</p>
</div>

{#- The distinctions come before the figures, deliberately. See foundation section 8.1. -#}
<ul class="panels">
  <li class="panel">
    <h2>Migration is not the same as asylum</h2>
    <p>Asylum is one route among several. Study and work were both larger in the most
    recent year. <a href="/common-claims/most-immigration-is-asylum/">See the figures</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li class="panel">
    <h2>Net migration is not arrivals</h2>
    <p>It is arrivals minus departures, a balance between two much larger numbers.
    <a href="/common-claims/net-migration-is-arrivals/">See why that matters</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li class="panel">
    <h2>A visa granted is not a person arriving</h2>
    <p>Permission is not a journey. Some visas are never used, and some are extensions for
    people already here. <a href="/what-the-words-mean/#visa-grant">What the words mean</a>.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>The headline figures</h2>

<p>Each figure below states what it counts and over what period, because without those two
things a number on this subject is not information. Each also shows its source, when that
source was published, and how much confidence the publisher places in it.</p>

<ul class="cards">
  {%- for card in dashboard.cards %}
  {%- set m = card.ref | metric %}
  <li class="card">
    <h3>{{ card.shortLabel }}</h3>
    {%- set symbolised = m.unit == "%" or m.unit == "£ billion" %}
    <span class="value">{% if m.unit == "£ billion" %}£{% endif %}{{ m.value | number }}{% if m.unit == "%" %}%{% endif %}{% if m.unit == "£ billion" %} billion{% endif %}</span>
    <span class="period">{% if not symbolised %}{{ m.unit }} · {% endif %}{{ m.period_label }}</span>
    <p class="means">{{ card.whatThisMeans }}</p>
    <p class="source"><a href="{{ m.source_url }}">{{ m.source_name }}</a><br>
    Published {{ m.published_date | longDate }} · <span class="grade">{{ m.confidence_level }}</span></p>
  </li>
  {%- endfor %}
</ul>

<h2>Before you compare these figures</h2>

<p>They do not all cover the same period, and two of them count people while others count
grants or events. Asylum, returns, visas and citizenship run to March 2026; net migration
runs to December 2025. Comparing across those windows and calling the difference a change
is not valid.</p>

<p><a href="/sources-and-method/">How every figure on this site is sourced and recorded</a>.</p>

